cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DB

The paper presents a general kernel framework for learning conditional rankings from various types of relational data, which involves optimization of squared regression and ranking loss functions. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and databases (cs.DB). Among these, machine learning and artificial intelligence are the most likely sub-categories as they are directly related to the proposed framework and algorithms. Information retrieval and social and information networks are also relevant as the paper discusses learning tasks in these domains. Databases is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on database management or query processing.
